description: We are pleased to offer this 1968 Mustang Custom. This is truly an absolutely beautiful resto-mod that was rotisserie frame off restored and assembled with meticulous care and attention to detail.  It has only approximately 1,000 miles on it since the restoration so it is still very fresh and new.  The show quality Cadillac Escalade Pearl White three stage paint shines perfectly. While it was on the rotisserie, the frame was powder blasted to get rid of any possible rust spots and antirust Rhino Lining material was sprayed all inside and underside of the car. The engine compartment was fabricated and shock towers removed to accept the rebuilt 1975 Chrylser big block 440 cubic inch V8.   A Mustang II power rack and pinion with outside coil over springs and shocks were added. The carburetor is a 650 Edelbrock sitting on an Edelbrock aluminum intake manifold and has a medium Thumper Cam. The transmission tunnel was altered to accept the Chrysler 727 automatic transmission and was rebuilt at the same time as the motor. The headers are international chrome. The heads were shaved and heavy duty valves and springs and a new crank was installed. The ignition is a high output electronic MSD ignition system. The rear end is a Ford 308 limited slip and was rebuilt with new hubs and bearings and has traction bars and heavy duty leaf springs. A new complete wiring harness was installed to make sure there were no bugs in the electrical system. It has 4-wheel power disc brakes and the front end is a new Probuilt full rack and pinion suspension with power steering. The exhaust is stainless steel Flow Master dual pipe system. The car has new doors, new glass, new floors, new dash and cluster, new hood, new truck lid, new gas tank, new blacked out chrome all the way around, new front and rear glass, a Flaming River stainless steel tilt steering column and has a new headliner with pad. A sound deadener was installed on the inside floor of the car before the carpets were installed. This car can cruise very nicely on the highway at 2100 RPM at 65 MPH. The black leather interior adds the luxury touch. It has new tires with Mustang Cobra wheels. You won’t find another Mustang like this.  All receipts and documentation is included.  The car is ready for cruising and going to car shows to win many awards! We can coordinate shipping anywhere. Please contact Savannah Classic Cars at 912-235-2347.

description: When Ford introduced the Ford Mustang in 1964 an instant love affair with the American Pony Car was born. The Mustang was smaller, lighter, and more nimble that any American manufacturer had produced thus far. This coupled with its fresh design, the Ford Mustang became a must have among the American public. 1967 marked a pivotal year for the Mustang, as this was the first time since the first generation made its debut that vast changes were made to the Mustang. Making it larger and having many more engine options than before. It also eliminated some things that did not make sense. 1968 was just the same and by this point, Ford had found the next best thing and had very little for competition comparatively. So iconic is the Highland Green fastback that Lieutenant Frank Bullitt drove through the streets of San Francisco, that Ford itself has done two modern versions of the Bullitt Mustang--the first in 2001, the second in 2008.

GR Auto Gallery is pleased to present this recently completed 1968 Ford Mustang GT tribute. It is hard to overlook all the details this car has had done to it. Starting with the exterior the paint has been done impeccably in recognizable and famous Highland Green, with Gold striping that follows the body lines on both the drivers and passenger’s side of this Mustang. According to the owner, no parts of the body have been replaced and the original metal is still intact and looking beautiful. All of the chrome accents look to have a mirror finish including the bumpers and accents around the whole car. Once you are done being in awe of the exterior the interior has been done to the same standard, coming in a new Ivy Gold with the carpet and seats looking like it rolled right off the line. The new and fully functioning gauges, as well as the Philco radio, pumps out the sound. Powering this time machine is a crate 302ci V8 that has all the getup and go, with added HIPO exhaust manifolds, an aluminum intake, and an upgraded AOD 4-speed automatic transmission with overdrive. This nut and bolt restoration was finished this year and is ready to get back on the road with a new owner, don’t pass this one up!
To see over 80 photos of this car, including under carriage please visit our website www.grautogallery.com

description: This 1968 Ford Mustang is one of the most interesting affordable classics you're going to see for quite some time.  With a bright factory color package, plenty of originality, and the control of a manual transmission, it's the perfect mix of vintage fun and standout appearance.

Acapulco Blue isn't just a cool name for your paint, but also this factory-correct color looks nice today thanks to a professional respray during its lifetime.  This sets up for a head-turning appearance that stays true to Mustang originality that also has plenty of the correct flair.  That's why the original bumpers and taillight bezels shine so nicely against the paint.  And speaking of shine, those GT-style wheels are arguably one of the best looking options the factory offered.  And since this is a '68, it was one of the few years of the sought-after Deluxe hood.  There's just something extra cool about those rear facing louvers that contain the turn signal indicators.

Inside, this one has all the right premium touches.  It starts with a two-tone blue interior that coordinates nicely with the exterior paint.  This factory-correct appearance looks great on the bucket seats, door panels, carpeting, and dash.  And keen eyes will spot the upgrade to a matching modern center console with cup holders â€“ a great place to rest your arm while your right hand is on the shifter.  The driver gets an updated three-spoke sports steering for better grip and flash.  Beyond that is the larger round gauge package that came on later versions of the first-gen Mustangs.  Plus, you get some great features like an upgraded AM/FM/cassette stereo that still has Mustang markings, and there are even provisions for factory air conditioning.

This is a C-code Mustang, and so you get Ford's 289 cubic-inch V8 under the hood.  It looks fantastically original and keeps with this car's blue paint scheme with its big blue block, blue air grabber, and the correct Powered by Ford valve covers.  And with all the correct decals and marking â€“ right down to the tag on the A/C compressor â€“ you'll really love showing off the engine bay.  But more than look great, there is a long maintenance record on this vehicle that proves it has been driven with care for decades (call for all the details.) That's why this one fires up nicely, drives with confidence, and you even get to unleash the sporty attitude with the three-speed manual transmission.

Complete with owner's manual and maintenance records, this is the iconic classic with a standout color package.  But while this car has plenty of blue, the only way it can make you feel blue is if you miss out on this deal.  Call today!!!

This Mustang is powered by a fortified 289 V8 fed by a 4 barrel carburetor, the powered is transferred via a 3-speed automatic transmission and delivered by a Ford 9' rear end.
